    "The plugins to be used for each PanDA queue are specified in the Harvester configuration.",
    "Experts of each resource develop their dedicated plugins and submit the code to the Harvester GitHub repository.",
    "Currently, there are plugins available for HTCondor, ARC Control Tower, Kubernetes [44], SLURM [45], PBS [46], and Lancium [47].",
    "PanDA DatabaseOperations are check-pointed and persisted on a transactional database shared by all the PanDA and JEDI servers.The database contains the state for all the jobs and tasks, related metadata for files and datasets, as well as information for other entities like users and sites.",
    "PanDA supports Oracle and PostgreSQL as database backends."
